HEADWORD: Incised
<hw>In*cised"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Cut in;
carved; engraved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having deep and sharp notches, as
